1) Create an app on facebook and activate sandbox mode
2) Change everything on your settings.py that is inside <> to your configuration

TEMPLATE_DIRS = (
    '<YOUR-DJANGO-PROJECT>/django-fukinbook/templates',
)

AUTHENTICATION_BACKENDS = (
    '<YOUR-DJANGO-PROJECT>.django-fukinbook.backends.FacebookBackend',
    'django.contrib.auth.backends.ModelBackend',
)

INSTALLED_APPS = (
    'django.contrib.auth',
    'django.contrib.contenttypes',
    'django.contrib.sessions',
    'django.contrib.sites',
    'django.contrib.messages',
    'django.contrib.staticfiles',
    'django-fukinbook',
    'django.contrib.admin',
)

FACEBOOK_APP_ID = '<YOUR-APP-ID>'
FACEBOOK_APP_SECRET = '<YOUR-APP-SECRET>'
FACEBOOK_REDIRECT_URI = 'http://127.0.0.1:8000/login/' # NOTE IT IS NOT localhost:8000 - It's because I put 127.0.0.1:8000 on my facebook application URL

3) Change your urls.py

from django.conf.urls.defaults import patterns, include, url
from django.contrib import admin
admin.autodiscover()

urlpatterns = patterns('',
    url(r'^login/', 'fukinbook_app.views.login'),
    url(r'^yay/', 'fukinbook_app.views.yay'),
    url(r'^admin/', include(admin.site.urls)),
)

4) python manage.py syncdb
5) Go to browser and type http://127.0.0.1/login/

Just got everything from http://djangosnippets.org/snippets/2065/
Thanks to http://djangosnippets.org/users/barnardo/
